    # "Out of the many emotions she expected she would feel, Sarah only felt one she had not expected."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c57d0fe0:
    # "Calm."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_af50c37e:
    # "For the first time in a long time, everything simply felt right to her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_09f0fbb6:
    # "There were no more questions to be settled of what came next. How she would survive. No more decisions to be made."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_53c69855:
    # "Turning her head to the side, she saw her new husband, sitting on the floor of the church, recovering same as her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_0cedf0f8:
    # "He looked back at her, grinning."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_9285d1e5:
    # "She smiled."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_640879e9:
    # "This was what she could have, if she just stopped overthinking everything. Stopped worrying about what should be, or what others thought."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e6878a5c:
    # "When she looked at him, she could see all the reasons for why he was wrong for her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_82050c16:
    # "But none of it seemed to matter, for she loved him in spite of all of it."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c8aa1824:
    # "Atop the altar, Sarah's mind drifted towards what had once been a nightmare, but now a dream."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_f06cf779:
    # "She rubbed her stomach in eager anticipation."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_6e8358f2:
    # "It was several days later when the deal on the house closed."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_b0fadbe2:
    # "Belmont was many things, but when it came to money, Sarah knew he had a talent for making it."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_3770f260:
    # "Sarah had taken to wearing her old dress again."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_28ef7576:
    # "It took her a bit to get used to not wearing her ship clothes, but Belmont insisted that no wife of his would look as if she worked for a living."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c1aa5d64:
    # "And Sarah quickly grew used to it again. It made a better fit for the role she was expected to play for her husband."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_2938c739:
    # "The house he bought her was small compared to the castle of her birth, but it was a respectable home in the small town of Northam."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_bb33a4d4:
    # "When he first showed it to her, Sarah could not believe her luck."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_dc0e1889:
    # "She ran through the house, exploring each room, and feeling her heart swell in a way it hadn't for a long time."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_cfa17ddc:
    # "A home. A safe place in this world that belonged to her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_f43b658a:
    # "To her and her new husband."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_d966a3ad:
    # "She walked back into the main room and saw Belmont grinning, happy with himself."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_8418eef7:
    # "Sarah leapt into his arms and kissed him, eager to show her gratitude for this gift."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_3cb41a1f:
    # "Later that night, she would show him her gratitudes in many ways more."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_751beab6:
    # "Walking the streets of Northam as a newly wed couple, Sarah could see the many ways the other citizens judged them."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_6bf5a79a:
    # "But no scandal lasts forever, and before long, Sarah and Belmont's marriage was old news and the citizens began to treat them more kindly."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_05d5a7bd:
    # "Sarah especially found a welcoming home in the town, managing to use her old talents of politicking to make her way into the social scene of the town."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c34ed8b2:
    # "She saw that none of them would ever understand what a girl like her saw in a man like him, but Sarah didn't care. It wasn't for them to decide."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_5f9a633b:
    # "For the first two months of their new marriage, Belmont delayed taking on any new contracts, remaining docked in the town of Northam."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_9bee1e64:
    # "Fearing missing their chance, the newlyweds spend every chance they got in their marital bed."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_923ebb34:
    # "But money had to be made, and so soon a contract passed by that was too good to ignore."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e6634afe:
    # "Sarah waved her husband goodbye and cried as his ship pulled beyond the horizon."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_357333f6:
    # "For the last few months, she had more of him than she could handle, and now she was suddenly all alone."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e7dc3d90:
    # "Never one much for religion, Sarah had now found herself praying most evenings, hoping for anything that might tip the scales."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_814d0519:
    # "Whether by nature or by divine hand, Sarah found her wishes come true."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_812854c3:
    # "With her husband still out at sea, her bleedings stopped and her body began to transform."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_0a923002:
    # "Strange and new to Sarah, she sought out the advice of the elder women in the town, who soon confirmed her suspicions."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_5f4f7968:
    # "Pregnant."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_3dfa1552:
    # "Each day, she could feel the life inside of her grow."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_7974433a:
    # "And she thought to herself, she was no longer alone."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_fbf742f6:
    # "When months later she received her husband's returning ship with eager heart, her body was already greatly different."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_ed310973:
    # "Her belly had grown large, and her breasts increased in size."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_3b65d0ef:
    # "Odd pains she'd never felt before, appeared all over her body, but she bore them with a smile."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_888af93f:
    # "For most of all, the child that had once been only a concept, was now large enough to be felt moving."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c01af1d2:
    # "She saw Belmont's eyes grow wide as he spotted her and realized the fact of her being."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_7de98723:
    # "There was rarely a more joyous couple in all the world."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_487ecce7:
    # "Belmont told her of all the news from the world beyond the small town of Northam, as Sarah fulfilled her wifely duties."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e2f9022a:
    # "Down on her knees, listening to him, she thought it odd."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_dbcc3bdf:
    # "Once she would have lived for stories of the world beyond the horizon, but as of late she had found herself instead turned inward."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_296f35a9:
    # "All the world was a footnote to the only thing that mattered to her, the inside."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_ae8d4d84:
    # "To her own surprise, Sarah found one of her fears to be unwarranted."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_b0611ebf:
    # "Feeling that her body was large, clumsy and bloated, Sarah feared that no man could ever love her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_49bc169c:
    # "But her husband, if anything, only seemed to desire her more."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_84fe72d4:
    # "Belmont delayed his next trip by several months, and Sarah felt her life fall back into a familiar bliss."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_393abe6d:
    # "It was only a little over a month when the child finally arrived."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_87538278:
    # "Surrounded by the older women of the town, Sarah survived a pain she'd otherwise believed would be her end."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c5ae3c82:
    # "The bed was drenched in the sweat and blood of her efforts."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_b69f7e2f:
    # "She could feel herself nearing collapse, but when she finally heard the screams of her child, all other things seemed to fade."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_133a9c66:
    # "The others smiled with joy, but she smiled with reverence."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_45f57ba2:
    # "Hers. Her child. She'd never known anything more divine."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_94f98130:
    # "A boy, they cried out."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_3042879d:
    # "She had given him a son."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_04c7f9bc:
    # "It should not have mattered, she thought, but she was glad still."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_7bcd4957:
    # "She watched as her husband, fearful of such a womanly situation, entered the room."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_bfc11bd7:
    # "For once, he seemed genuinely scared."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_659f6d6e:
    # "With great trepadation, he took his son into his arms."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e23ad755:
    # "The child reached out, grabbing hold of his beard, tugging on it slightly with what little strength it had."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_58797e03:
    # "Sarah watched as Belmont turned to her and smiled."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_21577581:
    # "A true smile, one imbued with all the love he had for her, and she received with all the love she had for him."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_5471169e:
    # "In the weeks that followed, Sarah felt her body slowly recover from the terrors of childbirth."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_3e22f0a0:
    # "Even her insatiable husband seemed to hold off for some time."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_8ff4b2e4:
    # "Whenever he looked at her, Sarah noticed something appeared to have changed."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_06a72c60:
    # "Out of the many ways that he had looked at her, never had he looked at her with respect."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e8d7b55e:
    # "Perhaps, she concluded, having delivered him a firstborn and having seen what she went through, he now had a different estimation of her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e5e6a810:
    # "Whatever it was, it changed little regarding how he treated her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_70d8b9f3:
    # "As soon as her body had healed, he began to take her as he always had. Sarah found herself grateful for it."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_cad73fdb:
    # "With the matter of a child now settled, Sarah found her husband using her in ways that were less suitable for progeny."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_098bd63c:
    # "Her mouth, her ass, spilling his seeds across her face."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_faae78fd:
    # "But Sarah was only glad. Glad that he still desired her for more than just her womb."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_26148f28:
    # "Regardless of how they did it, the frequency with which he took her made further pregnancies a matter of time."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_14af808a:
    # "Before long, Sarah found herself pregnant with a second child."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e6a069cf:
    # "Now burdened with raising his children, Sarah could manage his absences more easily. Loneliness was rarely a factor in a house now overflowing with life and energy."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_bf9716e1:
    # "Sarah found herself taking to motherhood in a way that felt both natural and easy to her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_30364f39:
    # "The many books she'd read, the many teachers she had back in Castle Reinmeer, all that knowledge she used to raise her own."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_71e0914f:
    # "She decided to keep her origin a secret, even from her own husband and children."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_47fe2ca4:
    # "In the end though, Sarah did not feel like she was lying. That life of a princess now felt so alien and removed from her, that it seemed like it belonged to someone else."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c247607d:
    # "For a few years, this was their rhythm."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_06fc65a0:
    # "Sarah bore his children, raised them in his absence. They would oscillate between periods where he was away at sea and where he was back on land."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_b06ec900:
    # "When he was away, she felt herself a mother. When he was home, a wife."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_1db3b939:
    # "It was some six years, and by now mother to three children, when Sarah watched her husband return one last time."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e9283fea:
    # "Belmont had ran into pirates and escaped only barely."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_d2d329fa:
    # "Realizing that his age had finally caught up to him, Belmont decided to sell his ship and retire, in no small part based on the urging of his wife."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_f0eb1275:
    # "The ship itself was in good condition, fetching them a large sum of money."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_d142e840:
    # "It was no fortune that would buy her a castle, but Sarah no longer dreamed of castles."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_5ac06179:
    # "It was however enough for her husband to stop working and make sure they would be provided for."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_723ffdf1:
    # "Sarah delighted at having her husband return to her, now without intermissions."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_7ece9538:
    # "Belmont, for his part, struggled with the reality of his own aging."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_fdd72593:
    # "As if hoping to prove himself still a man, he took towards fucking his younger wife."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_15aeb69c:
    # "Sarah knew he struggled, and bore his advances no matter how frequent they became."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_6bc898bb:
    # "In time, she felt her husband settle down into retired life."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_3c344311:
    # "He still took her frequently, but such was his nature, it had now simply ceased to be an obsession."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e41c53dc:
    # "Instead, to Sarah's surprise, she found her husband taking towards his role as a father."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_5f96e24b:
    # "She had seen many sides of Belmont since the day she first met him, but despite everything, he could still surprise her."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_fcc9a0cd:
    # "He played with them, taught them how to read the stars, and offered a more firm hand when Sarah's soft approach failed to keep their children in line."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e996cb29:
    # "With no more voyages out to sea, Sarah had her husband all to herself."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_4e65ae59:
    # "In little time at all, what had been three children soon became seven."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_4a410285:
    # "The townsfolk grew to love Sarah and her large family."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_fdf6e6fb:
    # "Though they always remained wary of Belmont and his more coarse behavior, they eventually settled on trusting Sarah's judgement."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_c23489ec:
    # "If she decided he was good enough for her, who were any of them to think otherwise."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_1a4dcb36:
    # "And so the years slipped by."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_701d514f:
    # "She never bore him more than seven children, but seven proved plenty."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_19fa7e7d:
    # "With each passing year, Sarah and her family grew ever more interwoven into the fabric of the small town of Northam."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_5041bcde:
    # "Going to school, taking on trades, eventually forming families of their own."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_7806538d:
    # "On the edge of the world, where nothing of concern ever happened, Sarah watched her family grow old and found her hapiness."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_b277e929:
    # "This is how she lived."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_60290271:
    # "So ends the story of Sarah Rose."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_e3b3d98a:
    # "Princess. Sailor. Wife to Belmont."
    ""

translate ru SailorPath10_241951e0:
    # "The End."
    ""

